==English==
===Etymology===
From French [[colossal#French|colossal]], formed from Latin [[colossus]], from Greek [[κολοσσος]] (originally used by [[w:Herodotus|Herodotus]] in reference to statues in ancient Egyptian temples).
[[Category:Latin derivations]] [[Category:Greek derivations]]

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/kə'lɒsəl/}}
*{{audio|en-us-colossal.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Adjective===
{{en-ad|colossal}}
#extremely [[large]] or on a great scale
#:''A single puppy can make a '''colossal''' mess.''

==== Synonyms ====
* (''extremely large''): [[enormous]], [[giant]], [[gigantic]], [[immense]], [[prodigious]], [[vast]]

==== Translations ====
;extremely large
{{top}}
*Finnish: [[valtava]], [[jättiläismäinen]]
*French: [[colossal#French|colossal]]
{{mid}}
* Russian: [[большой]], [[грандиозный]], [[громадный]], [[колоссальный]], [[огромный]]
{{bottom}}

